            <div class="row-fluid">
                <article class="span12">
                    <h1>Sociology Publishers</h1>
<p><span><span>Listed below are links to sociology publishers worldwide.  If you would like your organisation added to this list, please email <a href="mailto:donna.willis@britsoc.org.uk?subject=Please%20add%20my%20organisation%20to%20the%20list%20of%20Sociology%20Publishers" title="Email Donna Willis.">Donna Willis</a> <span>with a brief description and a weblink.</span></span></span></p>
<div>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.allenandunwin.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Allen and Unwin." rel="noopener noreferrer">Allen &amp; Unwin</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aaupnet.org/" target="_blank" title="Link to Association of American University Presses." rel="noopener noreferrer">Association of American University Presses</a><a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to Amazon." rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong style="color: #3e444f;"> </strong><span style="color: #3e444f;"> -The Association of American University Presses is an organisation of non-profit scholerly publishers.  This website provides a list of home pages for AAUP member presses, as well as several other academic presses.</span></a></li>
<li>BSA Publications Limited (the trading subsidiary for the British Sociological Assocation) publishes the academic journals <a href="/publications/cultural-sociology-journal/" title="Link to Cultural Sociology Journal.">Cultural Sociology</a>, <a href="/publications/sociology-journal/" target="_self" title="Link to Sociology Journal.">Sociology</a> and <a href="/publications/work-employment-and-society-journal/" target="_self" title="Link to Work, Employment and Society Journal.">Work, Employment and Society</a> as well as the book series, Sociological Futures.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/academic/academic-subjects/sociology/" title="Link to Bloomsbury Publishing." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bloomsbury Publishing</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.brill.com/" title="Link to Brill Academic Publishers.">Brill Academic Publishers</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cambridge.org/browse/default.asp?subjectId=1008600" target="_blank" title="Link to Cambridge University Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">Cambridge University Press</a> - Cambridge University Press is the publishing business of the University of Cambridge, one of the world's leading research institutions. It is the oldest publisher and printer in the world, having been operating continuously since 1584.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.degruyter.com/" title="Link to De Gruyter." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">De Gruyter</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.e-elgar.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Edward Elgar Publishing." rel="noopener noreferrer">Edward Elgar</a><a href="http://www.chandospublishing.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Chandos Publishing (Oxford) Limited." rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="color: #3e444f;"> - Founded in 1986, Edward Elgar Publishing is a leading international family publisher in the social sciences, specializing in research monographs, reference books, eBooks and upper-level textbooks in highly focused areas.</span></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.emeraldgrouppublishing.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Emerald." rel="noopener noreferrer">Emerald</a> - Established in 1967, Emerald Group Publishing Limited publishes over 700 titles comprising 200 journals, nearly 300 books and more than 200 books series as well as an extensive range of online products and services. </li>
<li><a href="http://www.footprint.com.au/" target="_blank" title="Link to Footprint Books." rel="noopener noreferrer">Footprint Books</a></li>
<li>
<p><a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/sociology" title="Link to Frontiers in Sociology Journal." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Frontiers in Sociology</a> was launched in May 2016 and is an Open Access, Peer Reviewed journal. It is currently comprised of 7 different sections covering different areas within Sociology, including Sociological Theory led by Professor William Outhwaite, and Medical Sociology led by Hannah Bradby. </p>
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.harpercollins.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Harper Collins Publishers." rel="noopener noreferrer">Harper Collins Publishers</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.hoddereducation.co.uk/sociology" target="_blank" title="Link to Hodder Education." rel="noopener noreferrer">Hodder Education</a> is the second largest school publisher in the UK, trusted to help teachers and students learn through our wide range of high quality resources and training events. We support the sociology curriculum with A-level student textbooks and revision resources, Sociology Review magazine, and our online learning platform, Dynamic Learning<a href="http://www.interculturalpress.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Intercultural Press." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.hurstpublishers.com/" title="Link to Hurst." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Hurst</a></li>
<li><a href="http://mitpress.mit.edu/" target="_blank" title="Link to MIT Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">MIT Press</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.manchesteruniversitypress.co.uk/" title="Link to Manchester University Press." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Manchester University Press</a> - Founded in 1904, Manchester University Press is the third largest university press in England, and is known globally for excellent research in the Humanities and Social Sciences. Currently publishing over 170 books each year, as well as seven journals.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mhhe.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to McGraw-Hill." rel="noopener noreferrer">McGraw-Hill</a> - Website for the publication of Higher Education literature.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mup.com.au/" target="_blank" title="Link to Melbourne University Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">Melbourne University Press</a><a href="http://www.openup.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to Open University Press." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.oup.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to the Oxford University Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">Oxford University Press</a><strong> </strong>- The Oxford University Press is a department of the University of Oxford, publishing books and journals worldwide.  In addition to publishing over 4,600 new books each year, Oxford is a major provider of online information to libraries worldwide.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.palgrave.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Palgrave Macmillan." rel="noopener noreferrer">Palgrave Macmillan</a> - Palgrave Macmillan has an established track record of international academic publishing, focussing on the Humanities, Social Sciences and Business. </li>
<li><a href="http://www.pearsonhighered.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Pearson Higher Education." rel="noopener noreferrer">Pearson Higher Education</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.penguin.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Penguin." rel="noopener noreferrer">Penguin</a> - The website for this established publishing house has sites for the UK, Canada, USA, Ireland, Australia, New Zeland, India and South Africa.<a href="http://vig.prenhall.com/home" target="_blank" title="Link Prentice Hall." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.polity.co.uk/sociology/" title="Link to Polity." target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polity</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.routledge.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Routledge." rel="noopener noreferrer">Routledge</a> - Routledge publishes around 1,000 new books each year and has a backlist of over 7,000 titles in print. It has also developed a journal publishing imprint that has particular emphasis on the humanities, social science, business, management and economics subject areas.</li>
<li><a href="https://uk.sagepub.com/en-gb/eur/home" target="_blank" title="Link to SAGE Publications Limited." rel="noopener noreferrer">SAGE Publications Limited</a><strong> </strong></li>
<li><a href="http://www.springer.com/gp/social-sciences/sociology" target="_blank" title="Link to Springer." rel="noopener noreferrer">Springer</a> - a leading global scientific, technical and medical publisher, providing researchers with quality content via innovative information products and services.<a href="http://www.stmartins.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to St Martin's Press." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.taylorandfrancisgroup.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Taylor &amp; Francis Group." rel="noopener noreferrer">Taylor &amp; Francis Group</a><strong> </strong>- With offices in London, Brighton, Basingstoke and Abingdon in the UK, New York and Philadelphia in the USA and Singapore and Melbourne in the Pacific Rim, the Taylor &amp; Francis Group publishes more than 1000 journals and around 1,800 new books each year, with a books backlist in excess of 20,000 specialist titles.</li>
<li><a href="https://policypress.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to The Policy Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">The Policy Press</a><a href="http://www.coop-bookshop.com.au/" target="_blank" title="Link to The Co-op Bookshop." rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong style="color: #3e444f;"> </strong><span style="color: #3e444f;">- As a not-for-profit organisation aiming to improve social conditions, the Policy Press are committed to publishing titles that will have an impact on research, teaching, policy and practice.  Website also includes links to related sociological / social policy websites.</span></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.press.uchicago.edu/" target="_blank" title="Link to University of Chicago Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">University of Chicago Press</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.uqp.uq.edu.au/" target="_blank" title="Link to University of Queensland Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">Univeristy of Queensland Press</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.vernonpress.com/" title="Link to Vernon Press">Vernon Press</a><a href="http://www.wadsworth.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Wadsworth Publishing." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="https://westviewpress.com/" target="_blank" title="Link to Westview Press." rel="noopener noreferrer">Westview Press</a><strong> </strong>- Publisher of academic and college books in the social sciences, humanities and sciences.<a href="http://www.willanpublishing.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to Willan Publishing." rel="noopener noreferrer"><br /></a></li>
<li><a href="http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/Section/id-351812.html" target="_blank" title="Link to Wiley-Blackwell sociology section." rel="noopener noreferrer">Wiley-Blackwell</a> - offers an authoritative sociology books programme and 32 journals in sociology and directly related fields, plus more than 30 additional journals in disciplines of interest to sociologists.</li>
</ul>
</div>
                </article>
            </div>
